What will be the output of the following Java fragment of code?

```java
class Superclass {
    void display() {
        System.out.print("This is from Superclass ");
    }
}

class Subclass1 extends Superclass {
    void display() {
        System.out.print("This is from Subclass1 ");
    }
}

class Subclass2 extends Subclass1 {
    void display() {
        System.out.print("This is from Subclass2 ");
    }
}

public static void main(String args[]) {
    Superclass a1 = new Superclass();
    Superclass a2 = new Subclass1();
    Superclass a3 = new Subclass2();

    a2.display();
    a3.display();
    a1.display();
}
```

